Tin cup suit!  Do some research...Jarhead!<br><br>
Gort is fashionably clad in Shineola cans with some dashing accessories fashioned from Spam containers. He also uses WD-40 for that masculine scent (deodorant) and a splash of 3-In One oil as an aftershave.  He sports an eye catching &quot;Big Ben Clock&quot; cleverly fitted to his left wrist by a chrome plated tail rotor drive chain (now there's a man's watch!)<br><br>
No red white and green bowling shirt for him!(just learned that DZ aka Defrosted Zuccinni is sueing the U.S. Army for calling olives draub)  Nor, would Gort be caught dead in a gaudy elevator operator suit.. or orange bib front overalls with matching pumpkin stained brogans!<br><br>
Personally, I am anticipating him being featured as next month's centerfold in &quot;Mechanic's Illustrated&quot; and his acting debut as &quot;Tin Man&quot; in the upcoming flim epic titled, &quot;Does Dorothy,&quot; written by B. Spatz and directed by Pee Wee Herman.<br><br>
Understand that Tom Dier's agent called, (Agent Orange) and opted for &quot;Wingman&quot; to play the part of a pumpkin...but only if Pagemaker agrees to play a chicken.<br><br>
Cookie, enraged because he was denied a part..will serve as an usher at the grand opening.<br><br>
I, Tatekohomni Wambli, Whirlwind Eagle, have refused large offers to star as the tornado...because I DON&quot;T PLAY!<br><br>
